Want to build apps for Android devices? This book is the perfect way to master the fundamentals. Written by an expert whos taught this mobile platform to hundreds of developers in large organizations, this gentle introduction shows experienced object-oriented programmers how to use Androids basic building blocks to create user interfaces, store data, connect to the network, and more.

Youll build a Twitter-like application throughout the course of this book, adding new features with each chapter. Along the way, youll also create your own toolbox of code patterns to help you program any type of Android application with ease. 


